                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.2311/68.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">American Ambassador</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-09-30T12:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 30, 1912—12 noon</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>In compliance with the request of the Mexican Embassy here permission is hereby
                    granted for a brigade of Mexican Federal troops to proceed from Piedras Negras,
                    Coahuila, by rail to Del Rio and Marathon, Tex., at which points they will
                    reenter Mexican territory with the understanding that such troops shall traverse
                    American territory unarmed, their arms and ammunition being sent as baggage and
                    with a small detachment of American troops to accompany them on the train as an
                    escort. Inform the Minister for Foreign Affairs and add that appropriate
                    American authorities have been properly instructed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Huntington Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
